{"chunk_id": "3e0ff5d1-26da-49a0-9549-2b15e12e491d", "source_database": "ICMR", "document_title": "ICMR_NIN_Dietary_Guidelines_Real.pdf", "publication_version": "Latest", "chunk_sequence_number": 84, "content_type": "Medical Guideline", "language": "English", "text": "factors and should be fed to infants. /c63Breast-feeding reduces risk of infections. /c63It establishes mother-infant contact and promotes mother-child bonding. /c63It prolongs birth interval by fertility control (delayed return of menstruation). /c63Breast-feeding helps in retraction of the uterus. /c63Incidence of breast cancer is lower in mothers who breast feed their children. /c63Breast feeding is associated with better cognitive development of children and may provide some long-term health benefits. Breast-milk contains all essential nutrients needed for the infant; it provides the best nutrition and protects the infant from infections. Breast-milk is a natural food and is more easily digested and absorbed by the infant as compared to formula milk prepared from other sources.", "embedding": [-0.03334207087755203, -0.027651440352201462, -0.05403953418135643, 0.018273497000336647, 0.029529660940170288, 0.10548695176839828, -0.049910932779312134, 0.04925742745399475, -0.040169525891542435, -0.03565364331007004, -0.0297635979950428, -0.014508827589452267, -0.09992172569036484, -0.01994558982551098, 0.011726679280400276, -0.007507783360779285, 0.020675819367170334, 0.029750894755125046, -0.012145609594881535, -0.009349768981337547, -0.009667664766311646, -0.024995222687721252, 0.045973144471645355, 0.04775469750165939, 0.02538071945309639, -0.03239349275827408, 0.014597746543586254, 0.006402789615094662, 0.04487227275967598, 0.039722464978694916, 0.0026443004608154297, -0.03374853357672691, 0.043759237974882126, -0.04497373476624489, -0.12196265906095505, 0.054193709045648575, 0.05077178776264191, -0.03065177984535694, -0.041506532579660416, -0.011568136513233185, 0.036214325577020645, -0.017440253868